I think the issue is that the test is using the new-style environment variable names in the `from_env` function, but the test is only setting the legacy names. Let me trace through the from_env function more carefully.

Looking at the from_env function:```rust
pub fn from_env() -> Option<Self> {    // Try S3_* first (new naming), fall back to CODETETHER_S3_* (legacy)
    let bucket = std::env::var("S3_BUCKET")        .or_else(|_| std::env::var("CODETETHER_S3_BUCKET"))
        .ok()?;
    // ... rest of fields
```

So it tries `S3_BUCKET` first - if that's not set, it tries `CODETETHER_S3_BUCKET`. If neither is set, `.ok()?` returns `None`.

The test sets `CODETETHER_S3_BUCKET`, so it should fall back to that.

